The paper focuses on image classifiers and proposes a method for testing the safety of deep neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with adversarial examples, which are a common topic in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses safety concerns, which could place it in the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses game theory and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
